comments.text: I really like the idea of an AI agent as SaaS AI - that is, creating applications for things like sales phone calls, applications for fundamental analysis of individual publicly traded companies, etc. However, I think this requires very advanced programming skills - vibe coding can build a working prototype, MVP - so it needs a few months to master creating great applications in JavaScript - or wait for AI to do it at a very high level :), selling the AI agent or consulting maybe in a subscription model is a good and realistic idea - you don’t need to have high programming skills and a website along with perfect mastery of the AI agent is enough - but with the business model, you still need to analyze the competition and how companies currently building AI agents operate - superficially - the biggest successes come from AI agents in the style of Replit... so it's good if someone can program and also create automations at the highest level - then success is guaranteed. These things do not require large financial investments, but rather very high skills - a year may be enough to master JavaScript and an AI agent. However, realistically, it's better to start with the AI agent first because the competition is small and profits can be achieved even through lead automation or simply by creating chatbots and voice AI agents. Personally, I am interested in the idea of automating the entire company - everything, and that is a big topic.
